.TH "speaker_gain_put" 9 "speaker_gain_put" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
speaker_gain_put \- set the speaker gain setting.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" speaker_gain_put
.BI "(struct snd_kcontrol *kcontrol "  ","
.BI "struct snd_ctl_elem_value *ucontrol "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kcontrol" 12
The control for the speaker gain.
.IP "ucontrol" 12
The value that needs to be set.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the value of the speaker gain from the specified
\fIucontrol\fP setting.

Note, if the speaker amp is muted, then we do not set a gain value
as at-least one of the ICs that is fitted will try and power up even
if the main control is set to off.
